HEADWORD: Wangan
<hw>Wan"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[American
Indian.]</ety> <def>A boat for conveying provisions, tools, etc.; -- so
called by Maine lumbermen.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>wangun</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
